{"commentv2": 1, "number": 2, "id": 437675, "nreplies": 0, "sticky": 0, "user": "Gnub", "body": "I wonder why noone has noticed the obvious reference to the character Samson from the TV Show \"[url=http://www.imdb.com/title/tt0319969/]Carniv\u00e1le[/url]\". He is a very small man, and leads the place.\n\nLook closely, and you'll find alot of similarities around the Faire. Cards, for instance, is a very big part both of the place and the show itself.", "date": "2008-11-10T15:44:24-06:00", "rating": 25, "indent": 0, "roles": 256, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "lastEdit": ["2008-11-10T15:44:51-06:00", 1, "Gnub"]}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 3, "id": 733034, "nreplies": 0, "sticky": 0, "user": "Skelic", "body": "[b]Who this dawg is[/b]\r\n\r\nSilas Darkmoon is the founder of the Darkmoon Faire, an exotic bunch of wandering showmen, who together celebrate the wondrous and mysterious idiosyncrasies found in Azeroth. \r\n\r\n[b]Quotes[/b]\r\n\r\n[i]Step right up! Step right up! Greetings my friend. I'm Silas Darkmoon and I want to welcome you to the greatest show on Azeroth! It's the Darkmoon Faire friend, and it's your lucky day! Sparing no expense, we've gathered wonders and treats from around the world for your delight. Whether you're young or old, rich or poor, the Darkmoon Faire has it all!\r\n\r\nAmaze at the wonders that the Darkmoon Faire has uncovered in this vast and mysterious world! We have spared no expense in bringing you excitement that children of all ages will delight in!\r\n\r\nWe have it all... delicious food, strong drink, exotic artifacts, fortunes read, amazing prizes and excitement without end!\r\n\r\nAnd, don't forget to turn in your Darkmoon Faire Prize Tickets! All it takes is five or more and you're on your way to the most wondrous prizes on all of Azeroth. Everybody is a winner![/i]\r\n\r\n[b]Inspiration[/b]\r\n\r\nSilas Darkmoon may be (= is) a reference to Samson from the television series Carniv\u00e0le, played by Michael J. Anderson. Both characters are leaders of traveling carnivals, both dress similar and use a walking stick/cane, and both have similar stature. (Anderson has Osteogenesis Imperfecta, which made him very short.) \r\n\r\n[small]([url=http://www.wowwiki.com/]source: wowwiki[/url])[/small]", "date": "2009-05-31T10:08:01-05:00", "rating": 43, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
